<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Type locality. Bukit Panching, Pahang (
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="3.891111">3°53'28&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="103.14056">103°8'26&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Distribution range. Endemic to Bukit Panching (not seen in Figure 18A because its symbol overlaps with 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Diplommatinidae" genus="Plectostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectostoma senex" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="senex">Plectostoma senex</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Extinct. Its only 
<normalizedToken originalValue="habitat–Bukit">habitat-Bukit</normalizedToken>
Panching, has been completed quarried away (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Schilthuizen, M" journalOrPublisher="Tentacle" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="8 - 9" title="Tracking extinction from space." volume="16" year="2008">Schilthuizen and Clements 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The ruin is now inundated. The status of this species in a previous assessment (IUCN redlist) was: Critically Endangered B2ab(ii,iii) ver. 3.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="Clements, R" journalOrPublisher="Biology letters" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" title="IUCN 2013. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2013.2" url="www.iucnredlist.org" year="2009 a">Clements 2009a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
